Soronn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=garnishmintleaf>Garnish Mintleaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/01 6:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=455.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Jboot Help</span><hr size=1> I have obtained the &quot;ring of the ancients&quot; for J-boots for two of my own characters and many of my friends' on Rodcet Nife using the following method:<br>
<br>
First; Get up early while most people are still in bed (or stay up late after most people have gone to bed) to eliminate most of the KS competition. 4am EST is a good time.<br>
<br>
Second; There seem to be three PHs for the AC. Watch for &quot;a mummy&quot;. Not &quot;a crypt mummy&quot; or &quot;a shriveled mummy&quot;, just &quot;a mummy&quot;. Second is &quot;a madman&quot;, not &quot;a desert madman&quot;. And there is a third who's name escapes me right now... Might be &quot;a tarantula&quot; instead of &quot;a desert tarantula&quot;. Something like that, sorry that I can't remember. If you kill all three of the shortened-name spawns, the Ancient Cyclops will spawn shortly thereafter. Within a few minutes.<br>
<br>
The rest is easy, Everlore has a good guide for the remainder of the quest. I have never tried giving Bootstrutter plat instead of gold, but I have heard that it will work.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uartiethebold.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artie the Bold</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://brotherhood.rpg-guilds.com/artie/comets.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/01 6:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=455.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://brotherhood.rpg-guilds.com/artie/Artie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Jboot Help</span><hr size=1> It depends on your level and how good of friends you have.<br>
<br>
If you're in your 30's, then you're pretty much stuck with the South Ro camp. Bring friends and kill everything on the sand. Dervs don't seem to matter but everything else is open game. Some people say concentrate on undead ... I haven't seen any first-hand evidence of that; if it moves, kill it. Be prepared for a long time of running around killing things and keeping your eyes open for the AC, since he has a number of different spawn points. I have seen him at the following places: Along the east wall just south of the derv camp; between the west derv camp and the dark elf merchants; just west of the eastern derv camp; and in the vicinity of Ortallius in the northwest corner. There are probably other places he can spawn as well. Oh, and be prepared for other players to attempt to KS you, because they will. Bleh. (and by KS I mean jumping on it after you have engaged it. Killing things in the desert doesn't entitle you to first dibs if someone gets there first, which is why you want to bring friends and keep split up.)<br>
<br>
If you're at least 40 with a couple of similarly-leveled friends, do yourself a favor and get the OOT camp. You may have to wait longer for an AC to spawn there, but when it does you will not be in a contest for it. Also, the cyclops placeholders there will give you experience while you're waiting. There is one spawn point on the island, and it's on a six-minute timer if I recall correctly. Placeholders can be Cyclops (much tougher than those in Lake Rathe, these are in their low 40's), a pirate (low level), Boog Mudtoe (or Goob, one of the two, high-teens warrior ogre), aqua goblin (low teens or less), or your friend and mine, the Ancient Cyclops. If you are really good at holding the spawn, you can even pull a seafury or two in downtime, and probably certainly if you get one of the green /con placeholders (i.e., anything but Cyclops or AC).<br>
<br>
I strongly recommend the OOT camp if you can hold it, as the headache, hassle, and frustration are insignificant in comparison to the South Ro camp, unless you're really really lucky.<br>
<br>
Best of luck to you. The 'quest' (LOL) is a pain in the behind, but the boots are oh so nice! <p><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

