<br>
Turn your clipping all the way up, stand on hills and watch for the AC.  I have seen two in 40 minutes and I have seen none in 4 hours.  <br>
<br>
I sic my pet on one, and pull a second, I melee the second until the pet comes and then pull another.  A mage is a good class for keeping the sand red <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I would suggest keeping SOW up if possible, you want to be the first to the AC.  Hit it first and then yell for your group.  Good luck.<br>
<br>
 <p>Mezlo, Mage of 36 seasons, Drinal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useek9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seek 9</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 158<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/01 7:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=455.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.att.net/~jjperil/AnimatedGifs/torch.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Jboot Help</span><hr size=1> About SRo, /agree Mezlo.<br>
<br>
A couple things I want to add.<br>
<br>
The AC in SRo is near 100% resistant to fire spells.   Forget Blaze, Cinder Bolts, etc.  Go with the Shock line.<br>
<br>
If you have a group, you stand a better chance of getting the AC when it spawns, Rangers are especially nice here as they have the best track.  The downside of a group is that you are all likely to be rolling for looting rights, so you may lose out on that Ring.  Anyway, I was level 34 when I began the quest.<br>
<br>
When I went to SRo, the first time I zoned in, I saw the AC right away!   I started racing to it, and a stupid Dry Bones aggroed on my pet.  I foolishly stopped to kill the DB, and by then, the Dark Elf merchants killed the AC, what a fool I was.  I waited another 6 hours and the AC did not spawn that night.<br>
<br>
The next day, I brought a full group from my guild.  We killed everthing but the dervishes while awaiting the AC.  Nothing particular seemed to make him spawn.   Finally, after a few hours, it did spawn and we managed to get to it before the other groups.   We killed it and I lost the roll to the Ranger <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I then spent the next five evenings (in four hour camps) sitting on a sand dune letting my pet kill anything that came withing /attack range.  I endured constant threats from Necros, Wizzies and Druids (many in the 50s) saying that they were prepared to KS it.  Not much I could do about that due to the only spell available to me at the time that would work was low damage (Shock of Spikes).  I saw the AC on the third night, but someone else grabbed it in a massive KSing attack from someone else. <br>
<br>
Finally, on the 7th night, the AC popped near me, and I got to it first.  I did not even wait for my pet to engage before I started chain casting SoS at it.  Sure enough, a level 50 Necomancer was there only 20 seconds later and tried to KS it from me.  Fortunately, the first 20 seconds I had at the start were enough, and I outdamaged him.  He then ran &quot;inside&quot; the corpse with his pet and attempted to prevent me from looting it.  I clicked to loot and kept targetting him or his pet (what a friggin jerk).  He was trying to get the exclusive loot timer to expire before I could loot.   But, finally I was able to find a spot where the looting worked and I got the ring.<br>
<br>
That said, the Jboots are the best item I have, and the camp well worth the hell you go though in getting a pair, should you choose the SRo way.   I have died only once since getting them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Seek Pyremaker</b><br>
