<i>Elementalist of the 51st Summoning<br></i></body>
<body text=0/200/50><b>Tunare's Servant on Fennin Ro</b></body><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukalamos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/01 5:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=455.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Jboot Help</span><hr size=1> After reading this post I was inspired to finally get off my lazy arse and camp the Jboots this weekend.  Being that it was a holiday weekend and my having Monday off definately helped.  The following is how it turned out for me.<br>
<br>
I decided to give the South Ro spawn a shot as my lvl 52 Bard friend who was going to help me with the OoT spawn was busy.  I began at around 11:00am PST on Sunday ... summoned up and Earth pet and began the usual &quot;kill everything that moves routine&quot;.  I did this for many hours occasionally chatting in /ooc with the other people in the zone who were also camping him.  After lots of Sand Giants but no AC, I decided to take a break at 7:00pm.<br>
<br>
I returned at 10:00pm (had to watch X-files) and found out from one of the people also camping the AC that it had spawned about 10 minutes earlier but a Necro tryed to KS it and feared into the Oasis zone which for some reason caused it to despawn.  DOH!<br>
<br>
I again started running around killing everything.  As there was a Hate raid forming and the Wizzy portal the zone was packed with people and I felt if I even saw the AC it would get pounced on faster than Speedy Gonzalez.  <br>
<br>
But it never spawned .. 4:00am rolled around and there was only me and a lvl 8 in the zone.  I continued clearing out what ever I came across and at about 4:45am another SG spawned .. arggh .. so I dispatched him and then went to sit on the hill next to the DE camp.  Right when I was about to give up and call it a night, I heard more pounding footsteps ... I stood up, turned around and there was the AC strolling by just North of the DE camp.  My pet was at 20% and I was at 60% mana but I pounced on him and took him out quite easily.<br>
<br>
Here's a few things I'd like to point out ... after 15 hours on this camp I have to admit that there is probably no one way to make him spawn.  It's completely random ... but I do feel it spawns in one of the SG spots so you have to keep killing the SGs to make it spawn.  I don't know if the Undead Tower spawn has anything to do with it but the game night before the AC spawned I killed it and then turned around to see the named Sand Giant Husam spawn just after.  So I waited until the next night (was at 8pm gametime) to kill the Tower spawn again and it was shortly thereafter that the AC spawned (2 SGs had spawned that night before the AC did).<br>
<br>
Instead of myself in one spot hoping it would spawn near me, I chose to run in circles around the zone killing everything in my path.  I think this makes your chances better of getting to the AC first or running into one of it's possible placeholders.<br>
<br>
Im not saying that this wasn't purely coincidence, but on this camp you need all the mojo you can get.  If you decide on the S Ro spawn, definately try to do it in the wee hours of the morning.  If the AC had spawned 3 or 4 hours earlier I know I would have never got him for myself.<br>
<br>
I went to bed and did the rest of the quest the next day ... and am now the proud owner of JBoots.  Thanks for getting me inspired and good luck to the rest of you.<br>
<br>
